<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1538,2032]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,533,1646,1672]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Justification of the transfer.</emphasis>
Detailed examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[865,952,1647,1673]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gravely, 1931" authorityName="Gravely" authorityYear="1931" box="[991,1283,1646,1672]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sphingius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis box="[991,1116,1646,1672]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">S. longipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gravely, F. H." box="[1124,1283,1646,1672]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" pagination="211 - 282" refId="ref7267" refString="Gravely, F. H. (1931) Some Indian spiders of the families Ctenidae, Sparassidae, Selenopidae and Clubionidae. Records of the Indian Museum, Calcutta, 33, 211 - 282." type="journal article" year="1931">Gravely, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it has the typical somatic morphology for 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1893" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1893" box="[626,934,1682,1708]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cithaeronidae Simon, 1893</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[951,1030,1682,1708]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1709,1733]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,351,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-98@13.[151,1435,345,1686]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 10. Inthaeron longipes (Gravely, 1931) comb. nov., syntype Ƌ of Sphingius longipes Gravely, 1931. A habitus, dorsal. B eye group, dorsal. C endites, labium and sternum, ventral. D spinnerets, ventral. E labels from type bottle. F original illustrations adopted from Gravely (1931). Scale bars: A, 2 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4387699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4387699/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
A–D) and the diagnostic features of the monotypic cithaeronid genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Platnick, 1991" authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[521,800,1718,1744]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[521,630,1718,1744]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Inthaeron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Platnick, N. I." box="[637,800,1718,1744]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref7583" refString="Platnick, N. I. (1991) A revision of the ground spider family Cithaeronidae (Araneae, Gnaphosoidea). American Museum Novitates, 3018, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1991">Platnick, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as illustrated for 
<taxonomicName authority="Platnick, 1991" authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[998,1336,1718,1744]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossi">
<emphasis box="[998,1167,1718,1744]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Inthaeron rossi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Platnick, N. I." box="[1173,1336,1718,1744]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref7583" refString="Platnick, N. I. (1991) A revision of the ground spider family Cithaeronidae (Araneae, Gnaphosoidea). American Museum Novitates, 3018, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1991">Platnick, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the type species of the genus: highly coiled embolus, and embolus with a fringed flange (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1151,1226,1754,1780]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1036,1060]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,183,1013]" captionTargetId="figure-23@14.[151,1437,181,1013]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Inthaeron longipes (Gravely, 1931) comb. nov., left pedipalp of syntype Ƌ of Sphingius longipes Gravely, 1931.A prolateral. B ventral. C retrolateral. Abbreviations: E embolus, FF fringed flange, RTA retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bars: A–C, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4387703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4387703/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
A–C with 
<bibRefCitation author="Platnick, N. I. &amp; Gajbe, U. A." pageId="11" pageNumber="516" pagination="82 - 83" refId="ref7616" refString="Platnick, N. I. &amp; Gajbe, U. A. (1994) Supplementary notes on the ground spider family Cithaeronidae (Araneae, Gnaphosoidea). Journal of Arachnology, 22, 82 - 83." type="journal article" year="1994">Platnick &amp; Gajbe 1994</bibRefCitation>
: figs 1–3). Based on these observations, we propose to transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gravely" authorityYear="1931" box="[1026,1149,1790,1816]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sphingius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis box="[1026,1149,1790,1816]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">S. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[1185,1294,1790,1816]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1185,1294,1790,1816]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Inthaeron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="518" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1538,2032]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1826,1852]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[481,602,1826,1852]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sphingius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[481,602,1826,1852]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">I. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[611,742,1826,1852]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[611,742,1826,1852]" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be separated from the male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[1157,1236,1827,1852]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossi">
<emphasis box="[1157,1236,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">I. rossi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of features: broad retrolateral tibial apophysis (narrow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[933,1008,1863,1888]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossi">
<emphasis box="[933,1008,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">I. rossi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), fringed flange with a prolateral twist (fringed flange with retrolateral twist in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[610,687,1899,1924]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossi">
<emphasis box="[610,687,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">I. rossi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and absence of a median apophysis (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[1123,1201,1899,1924]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossi">
<emphasis box="[1123,1201,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">I. rossi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with highly reduced median apophysis) (compare 
<figureCitation box="[479,578,1934,1960]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1709,1733]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,351,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-98@13.[151,1435,345,1686]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 10. Inthaeron longipes (Gravely, 1931) comb. nov., syntype Ƌ of Sphingius longipes Gravely, 1931. A habitus, dorsal. B eye group, dorsal. C endites, labium and sternum, ventral. D spinnerets, ventral. E labels from type bottle. F original illustrations adopted from Gravely (1931). Scale bars: A, 2 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4387699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4387699/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="516">Figs 10F</figureCitation>
