<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">Note.</emphasis>
With the transfer of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[494,617,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sphingius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes">
<emphasis box="[494,617,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">S. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the total number of known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[934,1043,151,177]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[934,1043,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">Inthaeron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is increased to two, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Platnick" authorityYear="1991" box="[1360,1436,151,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Cithaeronidae" genus="Inthaeron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossi">
<emphasis box="[1360,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">I. rossi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Sankaran &amp; Caleb &amp; Sebastian" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[199,317,187,213]" class="Arachnida" family="Liocranidae" genus="Sphingius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipes" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,317,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">I. longipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[324,452,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[324,452,187,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; both species are known from both sexes.
</paragraph>
