<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">Remarks.</emphasis>
The ZSI collection has one glass bottle for this species labelled as “ 
<typeStatus box="[1093,1154,223,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">Type</typeStatus>
” (1513/18), containing a male specimen in good condition, with intact pedipalps. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gravely, F. H." box="[796,969,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="518" pagination="211 - 282" refId="ref7267" refString="Gravely, F. H. (1931) Some Indian spiders of the families Ctenidae, Sparassidae, Selenopidae and Clubionidae. Records of the Indian Museum, Calcutta, 33, 211 - 282." type="journal article" year="1931">Gravely (1931)</bibRefCitation>
also described the female of this species (
<figureCitation box="[160,259,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1709,1733]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,351,1682]" captionTargetId="figure-98@13.[151,1435,345,1686]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 10. Inthaeron longipes (Gravely, 1931) comb. nov., syntype Ƌ of Sphingius longipes Gravely, 1931. A habitus, dorsal. B eye group, dorsal. C endites, labium and sternum, ventral. D spinnerets, ventral. E labels from type bottle. F original illustrations adopted from Gravely (1931). Scale bars: A, 2 mm; B, 0.2 mm; C–D, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4387699" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4387699/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="518">Fig. 10F</figureCitation>
), but we could not trace any female specimen in the collection.
</paragraph>
